<br>
Due to the nice UI that shows my mana as a %age number, I don't need to worry about algebra...I see the following information on my screen.<br>
<br>
8:15pm<br>
Mana 51%<br>
Cast MS2, and Reclaim<br>
Mana 55%.<br>
<br>
For the longest time I get 4% back each pet.<br>
<br>
8:20pm AA DING! WOOT!<br>
I buy IM. Excited to see the improvement!<br>
Mana 61%<br>
Cast MS2, and Reclaim<br>
Mana 61%!!!!<br>
<br>
OMG! <br>
<br>
I'm so spun out.<br>
<br>
I personally have no interest whatsoever in improved reclaim of an injured pet. Since I discovered Reclaiming at the time Monster Summoning came out, I don't play that way. I don't chain pet much and when I do I just type /pet get lost, cast new pet and just before my pet appears, I hit return. 1 second or less between pets. When I'm down on mana, I reclaim for mana and move on. I am now forced to become a chain petter, which I only like in mage groups, and the benefit of Pet Cannibalization, or Reclaiming as I call it, during raids after summoning gear and CoHs to quickly recover mana (far more useful and frequent a usage for me, than chain petting to a lesser efficiency in timing which I don't do all that much anyway) is no longer available (unless, as I have been told by some illogical people, I spend alot more AA's elsewhere and spend money on getting gear for improved focus effects, thereby spending enormous effort to get me NOT QUITE to where I was before having to devote my resourses to fixing myself). All this stuff is a matter of personal preference and style really. Reclaiming or Chain-Peting. I'm a Reclaimer by style and perference.  So which is better or worse is not the issue.<br>
<br>
I petitioned and am hoping that Verant will reimburse me my AA's since I feel I was misled as to its usage, and spend it on a more useful skill like, I don't know...Lint Collecting, or Bird Watching.<br>
<br>
My dream of SCM3, SE3, Suspend Pet 2, Elemental Pact of the Reclaimer is out the window. Guess I'll just focus on Elemental forms to look cool.<br>
